Ask HN: How to charge for additional Enterprise iOS/Android App licenses?
text:
Hi. I am building a hardware device managed by a facility manager. The manager will decide which employee's smartphones will have access.

My plan is to make the App free for download and the facility manager will access our website to buy the tokens which they then give to the employees so they can connect to the hardware. I was going to use PayPal to process the credit card unless someone believes I should have more options like Google Pay and Apple Pay on my website.

But the question is, if the manager taps a link in the App that takes them to our website where the purchase is made, is that considered an In-App Purchase ? I don't think so because the token is for access to a hardware device (i.e., not a digital good), but I am unsure.

Ask HN: Should I be scared of you stealing my idea?
text:
Let's say I have a brilliant idea for an app that has real potential to take off, as it covers a known demand.

I have a working prototype. I know how to make it a real thing.

But I lack the time and resources to make it quickly.

"Ship it as soon as possible!", they say.

The worst possible scenario for me, that makes me skeptical of even posting about it until the product is ripe for market, is someone with more time, experience (incl. marketing experience) and resources stealing my idea and shipping it, only for me - the originator and innovator behind it - to be left and stranded bare-handed, unrecognized and forgotten.

Is this a realistic threat?
